name: stillwater-national-wildlife-refuge-stillwater-wildlife-management-area-anaho-island-natio-88b57
notes: The Fallon, Stillwater and Anaho Island National Wildlife Refuges are located in northwest Nevada and are administered by the refuge administrative office in Fallon, Nevada. Together they comprise the Stillwater Wildlife Management Area (SWMA). Water at Stillwater in 1965 was abundant. A number of significant events took place in 1965 which had an effect on the future water supply on the marsh including the temporary approval of a water distribution compact and several meetings involving interested persons and agencies.  Better water management has led to a record year of increased waterfowl populations. Botulism conditions compared to those of 1964 are much more favorable.  Construction consisted mainly of minimum, routine work. The grazing program in 1965 was little changed from the previous year. The total grazing use and revenue were up 9% and 7% respectively.
